A while ago I was in Dubai and one of my students, my Emirati students, was driving me home after

26
00:02:32,800 --> 00:02:38,240
a session and the car stopped at a light and she rolled down her window and she started shouting

27
00:02:38,240 --> 00:02:43,760
at someone outside of the window. This guy who was crossing the street with a big box of cloth

28
00:02:43,760 --> 00:02:49,439
and he started shouting back and she opened up the door and they started gesticulating and shouting

29
00:02:49,439 --> 00:02:53,840
at one another and I thought wow they're having a huge fight. I thought maybe he was going to hit

30
00:02:53,840 --> 00:02:58,640
her and she got back in the car and I said well what were you fighting about? And she said oh no

31
00:02:58,640 --> 00:03:03,680
we weren't fighting. He was giving me directions to your hotel and I thought that was a great

32
00:03:03,680 --> 00:03:11,200
example of how someone from another culture may misperceiver misunderstand something as a fight

33
00:03:11,200 --> 00:03:14,159
and in fact they were just being emotionally expressive.

34
00:03:16,719 --> 00:03:22,719
Just gesticulating what does that mean? It means what I was doing earlier waving your arms around

35
00:03:22,719 --> 00:03:28,640
to express what you're feeling. Aaron Mayer was worried because her student and the man on the street

36
00:03:28,640 --> 00:03:33,360
was shouting and gesticulating at each other. She thought they were having a fight when in fact

37
00:03:33,360 --> 00:03:39,840
they were just being emotionally expressive. And expressive means showing what you think or feel.

38
