You were nodding an agreement there Tim which reminds me of our quiz question in which country does

39
00:03:45,920 --> 00:03:55,360
shaking your head mean yes? Is it A Greece, B Japan or C Bulgaria? I said Greece. And that's the

40
00:03:55,360 --> 00:04:01,600
wrong answer I'm afraid. The right answer is Bulgaria. In some southeastern European areas such

41
00:04:01,599 --> 00:04:08,400
as Bulgaria and southern Albania shaking your head is used to indicate yes. In those regions nodding

42
00:04:08,400 --> 00:04:14,799
in fact means no as well. I hope I remember that the next time I meet somebody from southeastern Europe.

43
00:04:15,599 --> 00:04:21,120
Okay shall we look back at the words we learnt today? No hard feelings is something you say to

44
00:04:21,120 --> 00:04:27,120
somebody you have argued with or beaten in a game or contest to say you'd still like to be friends.

45
00:04:27,120 --> 00:04:34,560
For example I always get the quiz questions right unlike you Neil but no hard feelings okay?

46
00:04:35,519 --> 00:04:41,519
That's not a very realistic example Tim but I'll let it go. Number two to fall out with somebody

47
00:04:41,519 --> 00:04:47,519
means to argue or disagree with them. I fell out with my best friend at school. We didn't talk to

48
00:04:47,519 --> 00:04:53,199
each other for a whole week. That must have been a serious disagreement Tim. What were you arguing about?

49
00:04:53,439 --> 00:05:00,879
I can't remember. It was a long time ago. Number three a gesture is a movement you make with your

50
00:05:00,879 --> 00:05:06,800
hands or head to express what you were thinking or feeling. She opened her arms wide in a gesture

51
00:05:06,800 --> 00:05:13,599
of welcome or the verb I gestured to Neil that we only had one minute left to finish the show.

52
00:05:13,599 --> 00:05:19,279
Is that true Tim? You're nodding your head but we should also quickly mention gesticulate which

53
00:05:19,279 --> 00:05:25,919
means to make gestures with your hands or arms. A faux part is saying or doing something embarrassing

54
